Towers of Hanoi game sim. Codecademy project for practice with Stacks.
In this game, you are given 3 rods and a stack of four disks, each one larger than the last.
At the start, the disks are stacked in order of size on the leftmost rod.
Goal: move the 4 stacked disks from leftmost of 3 rods to the rightmost, ending in proper order of size.
rules:
1) Only one disk may be moved at a time.
2) Each move consists of taking the upper disk from one of the stacks and placing it on top of another stack or on an
empty rod.
3) No disk may be placed on top of a smaller disk.